</picture>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="eb-item__content">
                            <div class="eb-item__header">
                                <h4 class="eb-item__sub-title">
                                    
                                        News
                                     /
                                    <span class="eb-item__sub-title--normal">
                                        
                                            Carbon &amp; Climate
                                        
                                    </span>
                                </h4>
                                <h3 class="eb-item__title">
                                    <a href="/news/is-there-a-case-for-high-forest-low-deforestation-carbon-credits/" class="eb-item__link">
                                        Is there a case for &#8216;high forest, low deforestation&#8217; carbon credits?
                                    </a>
                                </h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="eb-item__standfirst">
                                
                                    The issuance of carbon credits just to forestall logging in highly intact forests is being scrutinised, as large volumes of such HFLD credits are expected to hit the market. Experts fret that they over-represent actual emissions saved.
                                
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <a href="/news/is-there-a-case-for-high-forest-low-deforestation-carbon-credits/" class="u-faux-block-link__overlay" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">Is there a case for &#x27;high forest, low deforestation&#x27; carbon credits?</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


                
            
        
    
